The axial displacement of the pendulum is induced by the plasma production, which corresponds to the thrust, and is measured by a laser displacement sensor. The detailed procedure can be found in ‘Method’ section. The absolute value of the thrust is obtained by multiplying a calibration coefficient relating the displacement to the force (see ‘Method’ section). The thruster efficiency ηT\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
